$$
\begin{aligned}
& f(x)=\left|\sin \left(\left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{6}\right) x\right|+\left|\cos \left(\frac{\pi r_2}{6}\right) x\right| \\
& f(1)=\left|\sin \left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{6}\right|+\left|\cos \left(\frac{r_2 \pi}{6}\right)\right|
\end{aligned}
$$

Possible value of $\left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{6}=\frac{\pi}{6}, \frac{3 \pi}{6}, \frac{5 \pi}{6}, \frac{7 \pi}{6}, \frac{9 \pi}{6}, \frac{11 \pi}{6}$
Possible values of $r_2 \frac{\pi}{6}=\frac{\pi}{6}, \frac{2 \pi}{6}, \frac{3 \pi}{6}, \frac{4 \pi}{6}, \frac{5 \pi}{6}, \frac{6 \pi}{6}$


(i) For $f(1)$ to be an integer
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \underbrace{\left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{6}}_{\frac{3 \pi}{6}, \frac{9 \pi}{6}} \\
& \frac{\pi}{6}, \frac{5 \pi}{6}, \frac{7 \pi}{6}, \frac{11 \pi}{6} \quad \underbrace{r_2 \frac{\pi}{6}}_{\frac{3 \pi}{6}, \frac{6 \pi}{6}} \\
& \therefore \quad \text { Required probability }=\frac{2}{6} \times \frac{2}{6}+\frac{4}{6} \times \frac{2}{6}=\frac{4 \pi}{36}=\frac{1}{3}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \text { (ii) } \quad f(2)=\left|\sin \left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{3}\right|+\left|\cos \left(\frac{r_2 \pi}{3}\right)\right| \\
& \left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{3}=\frac{\pi}{3}, \frac{3 \pi}{3}, \frac{5 \pi}{3}, \frac{7 \pi}{3}, \frac{9 \pi}{3}, \frac{11 \pi}{3} \\
& r_2 \frac{\pi}{3}=\frac{\pi}{3}, \frac{2 \pi}{3}, \frac{3 \pi}{3}, \frac{4 \pi}{3}, \frac{5 \pi}{3}, \frac{6 \pi}{3} \\
&
\end{aligned}
$$
For $f(2)$ not to be an irrational number
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \left(2 r_1-1\right) \frac{\pi}{3}=\frac{3 \pi}{3}, \frac{9 \pi}{3} \quad \text { and } \quad \frac{r_2 \pi}{3}=\frac{\pi}{3}, \frac{2 \pi}{3}, \frac{3 \pi}{3}, \frac{4 \pi}{3}, \frac{5 \pi}{3}, \frac{6 \pi}{3} \\
\therefore P(\bar{E})=\frac{2}{6} \times \frac{6}{6}= & \frac{1}{3} \\
\therefore P & =1-\frac{1}{3}=\frac{2}{3}
\end{aligned}
$$

Note: $E$ denotes event when $f(2)$ is an irrational number.

